<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ffe83b7e-7f86-4741-b401-dfcf4784bde4" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>F1D<xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:19:00" xt:id="66b1bc75-b89c-4c10-b4fd-992e54a75af2"/>6<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="66b1bc75-b89c-4c10-b4fd-992e54a75af2"/><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:19:00" xt:id="5b2425ee-f7d4-410d-a9c6-738fe41dd0d9"/>4<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="5b2425ee-f7d4-410d-a9c6-738fe41dd0d9"/></sptc><title id="_a6bf1822-527e-4a9a-af99-6cd40f7c97aa">Exposed joints</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_b4d52209-f363-4ca3-ac7f-280f45887f46" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e3e85244-b895-446b-80a3-372b9a2cef5f">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Exposed joints in the drainage surface on a roof, balcony, podium or similar horizontal surface part of a building mustâ€”</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_d21d24c2-2ff1-4f23-93da-da427de9481d"><xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-09-24T11:15:00" xt:id="96228518-9de6-4a21-a6a3-8aa64fac7057"/>be located on the ridge line or high point of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/9501_0.3.0.xml#_d3cc1a16-8ec1-4c83-9d06-a8c057409202" id="_07cd7a17-75b2-4afb-aadb-8339347099b0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">structural substrate</xref>; and<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="96228518-9de6-4a21-a6a3-8aa64fac7057"/></li><li id="_a5c8dc83-6ac7-47c1-a6f3-b7c6362f41cd">be protected in accordance with Section 2.9 of AS 4654.2; and</li><li id="_a6f71985-1630-414e-a6ff-08d7cb5447be">not be located beneath or run through a planter box, water feature or similar part of the building.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_3c105129-1f22-4d7e-be65-bfe40e8df2d6"><callout-type ncc-info-type="notes"/><p>For the purposes of F1D<xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:24:00" xt:id="c4e02de2-42c7-4008-b94a-517861ea884b"/>6<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="c4e02de2-42c7-4008-b94a-517861ea884b"/><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:24:00" xt:id="89c21f25-842f-4312-9cdb-eb7e323386ec"/>4<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="89c21f25-842f-4312-9cdb-eb7e323386ec"/>, an exposed joint is a construction joint, control joint, expansion joint, contraction joint or movement joint and includes an exposed joint which is directly below a drainage surface.</p></callout><callout id="_36044554-65ad-4ba0-89df-a210de22b642" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:type="delete"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:type="delete"/><title id="_b384be8a-0004-4207-8913-1686018856b9" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:id="8f5dce5a-62a9-4b7d-8b46-2ecafdab4a19"/>Location of exposed joints<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="8f5dce5a-62a9-4b7d-8b46-2ecafdab4a19"/></title><p xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:id="c4e2d846-2f6b-418d-bee7-706ec4579f37"/>To minimise the potential of water ingress, the exposed joint should be located at a ridge or high point of the structural substrate, where possible.<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="c4e2d846-2f6b-418d-bee7-706ec4579f37"/></p></callout><callout id="_501c8eac-d891-47ab-851d-b86324e298e1" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:05" xt:type="delete"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:05" xt:type="delete"/><title id="_c1743042-7bc7-4ba9-bef6-9ac12aa04cfe" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:05" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:id="86e1b25a-7db5-4544-8b32-e1d03e02325d"/>Exposed joints subject to excessive movement<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="86e1b25a-7db5-4544-8b32-e1d03e02325d"/></title><p xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:04" xt:type="delete"><xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:00" xt:id="8f05a4c4-0222-4993-80f3-3de85aeb0316"/>Where an exposed joint is subject to excessive movement, such as more than 10 mm, additional measures should be considered to ensure protection of the exposed joint. These additional measures may include use of a hob with a minimum height of 50 mm formed within the structural substrate for the full length of both sides of the exposed joint, and the exposed joint protected by a discontinuous <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4651_0.4.0.xml#_6e2c1aaa-5993-4850-908f-ac4007e94535" id="_5fa4b3f2-0070-4c37-b6d0-631e53e48558" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-03-28T09:25:04" xt:type="delete">membrane</xref> in accordance with Section 2.9 of AS 4654.2.<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="8f05a4c4-0222-4993-80f3-3de85aeb0316"/></p></callout></clause>